However, botanical drug interactions with other drugs have been reported and undesirable side effects may occur (
 Tachjian et al., 2010; 
 Ekor, 2014; 
 Lee et al., 2016; 
 Borse et al., 2019). At present, the World Health Organization has developed guidelines to reinforce safety monitoring of botanical medicines using pharmacovigilance systems, as well as encouraging quality controls during production by using modern manufacture techniques and applying good manufacturing practices (
 WHO, 2000, 
 2004).
